						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab built into the wall at Mēlina-maṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanamalla (Vikramāditya VI)—A.D. 1119.</p>						

						<p>The extant portion of this fragmentary record gives the details of the date as <hi rend="bold">[Vi]kāri, Vaiśākha, Amāvāsye, [Tuesday].</hi> These details are irregular. For the cyclic year falling in the reign of Tribhuvanamalla, the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1119, May 11, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift of land and garden to a deity (name lost) made after purchase.</p>						

						</summary>
